<paragraph id="D433956EFFF0FFCD60BDD842FEC7FE78" blockId="6.[151,518,328,387]" box="[151,295,362,387]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
(
<figureCitation id="4CB789EBFFF0FFCD60B5D842FEFEFE78" box="[159,286,362,387]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 20–31</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C96C6E5FFF0FFCD60BDD89AFC35FC80" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" type="description">
<paragraph id="D433956EFFF0FFCD60BDD89AFD74FDA0" blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="E6F8497CFFF0FFCD60BDD89AFEC9FE30" bold="true" box="[151,297,434,459]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Description.</emphasis>
Body translucent whitish overall. Vertex with two round opaque white patches between coronal suture and eyes. Pronotum with two symmetrical L-shaped opaque white patches. Scutellum opaque whitish medially; triangles pale yellow, terminal part of scutellum yellow. Forewing with basal half mostly opaque ivory, with large transverse reddish-brown medial band, apical cells transparent and infumated lightly; 1st apical cell smallest, 2nd apical cell largest (
<figureCitation id="4CB789EBFFF0FFCD622EDB6AFD68FDA0" box="[516,648,578,603]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 20–22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D433956EFFF0FFCD60EDDB4EFB19FCAC" blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
Abdominal apodemes nearly extending to apex of 7th segment. Pygofer side with several rigid setae at hind margin, and with large triangular lobe at ventro-caudal angle (
<figureCitation id="4CB789EBFFF0FFCD6379DBA2FC37FD58" box="[851,983,650,675]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 23, 24</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate with triangular lateral protrusion subapically, with 2 small rigid setae and 1 peg-like seta apically (
<figureCitation id="4CB789EBFFF0FFCD6420DB86FB71FD3C" box="[1034,1169,686,711]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 25, 26</figureCitation>
). Paramere with lateral margin broadly rounded distad of connective, medial margin with several irregularly arranged sensory pits, apex curved slightly and abruptly tapered (
<figureCitation id="4CB789EBFFF0FFCD6210DBDEFD6EFCF4" box="[570,654,758,783]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Fig. 28</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft bending gently and inflated near midlength in lateral view, with two pairs of processes; apical ventral processes long, slender and asymmetrical, one serrate apically and extended laterad, other curved to shaft; dorsal processes near midlength short and thin (
<figureCitation id="4CB789EBFFF0FFCD6443DA16FB0CFCAC" box="[1129,1260,830,855]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 31" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1878,1900]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,199,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[200,1387,195,1854]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 31. Guheswaria brevicula sp. nov. 20, habitus, dorsal view; 21, habitus, lateral view; 22, face of male; 23, male pygofer, lateral view; 24, hind margin of male pygofer, lateral view; 25, paramere, connective, subgenital plate and sternite IX, dorsal view; 26, apex of subgenital plate; 27, connective; 28, paramere; 29, aedeagus, posterior view; 30, aedeagus, lateral view; 31, apical part of aedeagus, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/259119/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Figs 29–31</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
