<paragraph id="D433956EFFF0FFCD60EDDADAFEBEFBA8" blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="E6F8497CFFF0FFCD60EDDADAFEF1FBF0" bold="true" box="[199,273,1010,1035]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Notes.</emphasis>
The reddish-brown pattern and genital characteristics of the new species are unique in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="138CEEEDFFF0FFCD60BDDD3EFEC0FBD4" box="[151,288,1046,1071]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Guheswaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E6F8497CFFF0FFCD60BDDD3EFEC0FBD4" box="[151,288,1046,1071]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Guheswaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
excepting that the crown with two large white patches and shape of connective are similar to 
<taxonomicName id="138CEEEDFFF0FFCD65AEDD3FFEBEFBA8" authority="Thapa." authorityName="Thapa." class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Guheswaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linguplata">
<emphasis id="E6F8497CFFF0FFCD65AEDD3FFEEAFBA8" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">G. linguplata</emphasis>
Thapa.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9C96C6E5FFF0FFCD60EDDD76FC6CFB60" pageId="6" pageNumber="259" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D433956EFFF0FFCD60EDDD76FC6CFB60" blockId="6.[151,1437,434,1179]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">
<emphasis id="E6F8497CFFF0FFCD60EDDD76FEAEFB8C" bold="true" box="[199,334,1118,1143]" pageId="6" pageNumber="259">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from a combination of the Latin prefix “brevi-” (short) and the Latin suffix “-cula” (small) which refers to caudal part of paramere short.
</paragraph>
